## Create virtual env
```python -m venv venv ```

## Activate it
On Windows:
``` .\venv\Scripts\activate ```

On macOS/Linux:
``` source venv/bin/activate ```

## Install dependencies
``` pip install -r requirements.txt ```

## Install npm dependencies
``` npm install ```

## Run Tailwind CSS build process
``` npm run tailwind ```

## Run Django development server
``` python manage.py runserver ```

## Additional Notes
- Ensure you have Node.js and npm installed on your system.
- The `tailwindcss` command will watch for changes in your CSS files and recompile them automatically.
- Flowbite and Preline are included in the npm dependencies and will be available for use in your project.
- Flowbite and Preline are included in the npm dependencies and will be available for use in your project.
- Ensure that the `node_modules` folder is placed in the `static` folder.